The Herald Walter Mswazie in Masvingo
The number of cattle that have succumbed from Anthrax attack in Bikita in Masvingo province has risen to 40 from 24 last week while 33 people have also been diagnosed with the deadly disease. Bikita District Development Coordinator Mr Benard Hadzirambwi confirmed the new developments and said government has since availed 5000 vaccines. <img class="size-full wp-image-410375" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/01/0601-1-1-ANTHRAX.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/01/0601-1-1-ANTHRAX.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/01/0601-1-1-ANTHRAX-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> An anthrax ridden cow “We have experienced an increase in people diagnosed with anthrax from 28 to 33 while cattle deaths have also risen to 40 from 24,” said Mr Hadzirambwi. He said Government has availed 5000 vaccines for administering on the district herd
